// @trap :9:0
// `__trap__()` → `unreachable`: the deliberate abort primitive (std-design D1
// OD2 — `std:test`'s failure path; a richer `panic(msg)` can subsume it).
// Execution reaches the call and the program aborts with a wasm trap mapped to
// this source location; the trailing print must never run. (The mapped REASON
// text is shared with bounds-check traps — both lower to `unreachable` — so
// only the location is pinned here.)
const x = 1
__trap__()
print(x)
